section.section:
Except as permitted under paragraph (b) of this subsection, an applicant or license holder shall pay to the department the following annual license fees:
Thirty dollars ($30) for each taxicab, limousine, TNC, or disabled persons vehicle;
Ten dollars ($10) for each motor carrier vehicle transporting household goods for hire;
One hundred dollars ($100) for each charter bus or bus;
Fifteen dollars ($15) for each motor carrier vehicle operating as a U-Drive-It;
Ten dollars ($10) for each motor carrier vehicle transporting property other than household goods and those exempt under KRS 281.605;
Ten dollars ($10) for each motor carrier vehicle operating as a driveaway; and
Ten dollars ($10) for each automobile utility trailer.
